<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="1353" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1353">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/144.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to Consul <persName type="to">Letcher</persName>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-23">
                                        <hi rend="italic">January 23, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Ascertain and report whether authorities made the promised
                                investigation of murder of Spanish subjects, and if so, as to
                                outcome. If investigation not made, informally urge that it should
                                be made at once.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>